nt primary Soviet documents dealing with the brutal economic and cultural subjugation of the Russian peasantry. Drawn from previously unavailable and in many cases unknown archives, these harrowing documents provide the first unimpeded view of the experience of the peasantry during the years 1927-1930.The book, the first of four in the series, covers the background of collectivization, its violent implementation, and the mass peasant revolt that ensued. For its insights into the horrific fate of the Russian peasantry and into Stalin’s dictatorship, The War Against the Peasantry takes its place an as unparalleled resource.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCollectivization of agriculturezSoviet UnionxHistoryvSources. 0aPeasantszSoviet UnionxHistoryvSources. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aDanilov, V. P., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aIvnitskii, N. A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKozlov, Denis, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aShabad, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aViola, Lynne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aViola, Lynne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030010612140uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030012782940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300127829423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300127829/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY